hh3cDHCPServer.name: hh3cDHCPServer
hh3cDHCPServer.contactinfo: Platform Team H3C Technologies Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.h3c.com Zip: 100085
hh3cDHCPServer.description: The MIB module is used for DHCP server.

hh3cDHCPServerIPPoolUsage.name: hh3cDHCPServerIPPoolUsage
hh3cDHCPServerIPPoolUsage.description: Usage factor of DHCP server ip pool.

hh3cDHCPServerReqTimes.name: hh3cDHCPServerReqTimes
hh3cDHCPServerReqTimes.description: Number of requests received by the DHCP server.

hh3cDHCPServerReqSuccessTimes.name: hh3cDHCPServerReqSuccessTimes
hh3cDHCPServerReqSuccessTimes.description: Number of requests success responses sent by the DHCP server.

hh3cDHCPServerAvgIpUseThreshold.name: hh3cDHCPServerAvgIpUseThreshold
hh3cDHCPServerAvgIpUseThreshold.description: Threshold of average IP usage of a DHCP server pool in 5 minutes.

hh3cDHCPServerMaxIpUseThreshold.name: hh3cDHCPServerMaxIpUseThreshold
hh3cDHCPServerMaxIpUseThreshold.description: Threshold of maximum IP usage of a DHCP server pool in 5 minutes.

hh3cDHCPServerAllocateThreshold.name: hh3cDHCPServerAllocateThreshold
hh3cDHCPServerAllocateThreshold.description: Threshold of DHCP server allocated IP address in 5 minutes.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolTable.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolTable
hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolTable.description: A table for creating DHCP server global pools.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolEntry.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolEntry
hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolEntry.description: An entry containing objects for creating or deleting a global pool for the DHCP server.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolRowStatus.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolRowStatus
hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolConfigTable.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolConfigTable
hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolConfigTable.description: A table containing the configurations of dhcp server global pools.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolConfigEntry.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolConfigEntry
hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolConfigEntry.description: An entry containing the objects for configuring the network ip or host ip etc. to global pools for DHCP server.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolType.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolType
hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolType.description: Type of a DHCP global pool. Any operations of this object will be bound with the operations of hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolNetwork, hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolHostIPAddr, or hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolHostHAddr. That means any operation of this object alone will be regarded as invalid operation.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolNetwork.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolNetwork
hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolNetwork.description: Network ip of a DHCP global pool. To delete a configured network ip, please set hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolCfgUndoFlag to 1.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolNetworkMask.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolNetworkMask
hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolNetworkMask.description: Net mask of a DHCP global pool(network). The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET of hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolNetwork together, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation. When a network ip of a DHCP global pool was deleted, the net mask would also be deleted automatically, and no further operation needed.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolHostIPAddr.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolHostIPAddr
hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolHostIPAddr.description: Host ip of a DHCP global pool. To delete a configured network ip, please set hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolCfgUndoFlag to 2.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolHostMask.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolHostMask
hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolHostMask.description: Net mask of a DHCP global pool(host) The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET of hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolHostIPAddr together, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation. When a host ip of a DHCP global pool was deleted, the net mask would also be deleted automatically, and no further operation needed.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolHostHAddr.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolHostHAddr
hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolHostHAddr.description: Hardware address of a DHCP global pool(host). To delete a configured hardware address, please set hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolCfgUndoFlag to 3.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolCfgUndoFlag.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolCfgUndoFlag
hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolCfgUndoFlag.description: Flag of undo operation for hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolConfigTable.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolStartAddr.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolStartAddr
hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolStartAddr.description: Start IP of a DHCP global pool. To delete a configured start IP, please set hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolStartAddr to 0. It takes effect only when hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolNetwork is set.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolEndAddr.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolEndAddr
hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolEndAddr.description: End ip of a DHCP global pool.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolAllocObject.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolAllocObject
hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolAllocObject.description: A DHCP global pool type for object allocated address. User: the DHCP global pool allocates address for user. Admin: the DHCP global pool allocates address for route or switch. The default value is 0.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolParaTable.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolParaTable
hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolParaTable.description: A table for configuring parameters to DHCP global pools.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolParaEntry.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolParaEntry
hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolParaEntry.description: An entry containing the objects for the configurations of parameters of DHCP global pools.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseDay.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseDay
hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseDay.description: Number of days of the lease.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseHour.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseHour
hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseHour.description: Number of hours of the lease.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseMinute.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseMinute
hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseMinute.description: Number of minutes of the lease.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseUnlimited.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseUnlimited
hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseUnlimited.description: A flag denoting if the lease of a pool is unlimited.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliGWIPStr.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliGWIPStr
hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliGWIPStr.description: String of gateway ip addresses for DHCP clients. Since mostly 8 ip can be configured for a pool totally, a string is defined to get or configure 8 ip ip at a time.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliGWIPUndo.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliGWIPUndo
hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliGWIPUndo.description: A gateway ip address to delete. This object is only for deleting a given ip of gateway router.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliDNSIPStr.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliDNSIPStr
hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliDNSIPStr.description: String of DNS server ip addresses for DHCP clients. Since mostly 8 ip can be configured for a pool totally, a string is defined to get or configure 8 ip at a time.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliDNSIPUndo.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliDNSIPUndo
hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliDNSIPUndo.description: A DNS server ip address to delete. This object is only for deleting a given ip of DNS server.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliNetbiosType.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliNetbiosType
hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliNetbiosType.description: NetBios node type for DHCP clients.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliNbnsIPStr.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliNbnsIPStr
hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliNbnsIPStr.description: String of NetBios server ip addresses for DHCP clients. Since mostly 8 ip can be configured for a pool totally, so a string is defined to get or configure 8 ip at a time.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliNbnsIPUndo.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliNbnsIPUndo
hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliNbnsIPUndo.description: A NetBios server ip address to delete. This object is only for deleting a given ip of NetBios server.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolIPInUseReset.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolIPInUseReset
hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolIPInUseReset.description: Reset the auto binding ip of the given global pool for DHCP server.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseTime.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseTime
hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseTime.description: Number of timeticks of the lease.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolPrimaryDNSIP.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolPrimaryDNSIP
hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolPrimaryDNSIP.description: The Primary DNS server IP address to be assigned to the client. To delete a configured Primary DNS server IP, please set hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolPrimaryDNSIP to 0. It takes effect only when hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolNetwork is set.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolSecondaryDNSIP.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolSecondaryDNSIP
hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolSecondaryDNSIP.description: The Secondary DNS server IP address to be assigned to the client. To delete a configured Secondary DNS server IP, please set hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolSecondaryDNSIP to 0. It takes effect only when hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolNetwork is set.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseSecond.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseSecond
hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseSecond.description: Number of seconds of the lease.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseTimeSec.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseTimeSec
hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolLeaseTimeSec.description: Number of seconds of the lease. The default value is 86400

hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliGWIPAddr.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliGWIPAddr
hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolCliGWIPAddr.description: Ip addresses of gateway for DHCP clients.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolOptionTable.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolOptionTable
hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolOptionTable.description: A table for configuring options to DHCP global pools.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolOptionEntry.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolOptionEntry
hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolOptionEntry.description: An entry containing the objects for configuring options to DHCP global pools.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolOptHexString.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolOptHexString
hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolOptHexString.description: Hex string of an option. 1st to 16th hex strings, which are 2 bytes, 4 bytes, 6 bytes or 8 bytes, can be configured at most simultaneously. That means the format of each string must be '12', '1234', '123456' or '12345678'.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolOptIPString.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolOptIPString
hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolOptIPString.description: IP string of an option. 1 to 8 ip addresses can be configured at most simultaneously.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolOptRowStatus.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolOptRowStatus
hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolOptRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolStatTable.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolStatTable
hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolStatTable.description: The statistics of each DHCP address pool.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolStatEntry.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolStatEntry
hh3cDHCPSrvGlobalPoolStatEntry.description: An entry containing the statistics of each DHCP address pool.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolIPPoolUsage.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolIPPoolUsage
hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolIPPoolUsage.description: Utilization rate of IP addresses in each DHCP address pool, in percentage.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolReqTimes.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolReqTimes
hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolReqTimes.description: Number of request packets received by each DHCP address pool, including the request packets for an extension of the lease.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolSuccessTimes.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolSuccessTimes
hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolSuccessTimes.description: Number of positive responses sent by each DHCP address pool, including responses to the request for an extension of the lease.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolDiscoverTimes.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolDiscoverTimes
hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolDiscoverTimes.description: Number of discover packets received by each DHCP address pool.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolOfferTimes.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolOfferTimes
hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolOfferTimes.description: Number of offer packets sent by each DHCP address pool.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolACKTimes.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolACKTimes
hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolACKTimes.description: Number of ACK packets sent by each DHCP address pool.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolTotalIpNum.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolTotalIpNum
hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolTotalIpNum.description: Number of IP addresses in each DHCP address pool.

hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolInUsedIpNum.name: hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolInUsedIpNum
hh3cDHCPSrvGlbPoolInUsedIpNum.description: Number of allocated IP addresses in each DHCP address pool.

hh3cDHCPSvrOptionGroupTable.name: hh3cDHCPSvrOptionGroupTable
hh3cDHCPSvrOptionGroupTable.description: A table for creating DHCP server global option groups.

hh3cDHCPSvrOptionGroupEntry.name: hh3cDHCPSvrOptionGroupEntry
hh3cDHCPSvrOptionGroupEntry.description: An entry containing objects for creating or deleting a global option group.

hh3cDHCPSvrOptionGroupRowstatus.name: hh3cDHCPSvrOptionGroupRowstatus
hh3cDHCPSvrOptionGroupRowstatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy.

hh3cDHCPSvrOptionTable.name: hh3cDHCPSvrOptionTable
hh3cDHCPSvrOptionTable.description: A table for configuring options in a global option group.

hh3cDHCPSvrOptionEntry.name: hh3cDHCPSvrOptionEntry
hh3cDHCPSvrOptionEntry.description: An entry containing objects for configuring an option in a global option group.

hh3cDHCPSvrOptionHexString.name: hh3cDHCPSvrOptionHexString
hh3cDHCPSvrOptionHexString.description: Hex string of an option. 1 to 16 hex strings, which are 2 bytes, 4 bytes, 6 bytes or 8 bytes, can be configured at most simultaneously. That means the format of each string must be '12', '1234', '123456' or '12345678'.

hh3cDHCPSvrOptionIPString.name: hh3cDHCPSvrOptionIPString
hh3cDHCPSvrOptionIPString.description: Ip string of an option. 1 to 8 ip addresses can be configured at most simultaneously.

hh3cDHCPSvrOptionRowstatus.name: hh3cDHCPSvrOptionRowstatus
hh3cDHCPSvrOptionRowstatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy.

hh3cDHCPSvrVerifyMacTable.name: hh3cDHCPSvrVerifyMacTable
hh3cDHCPSvrVerifyMacTable.description: A table containing the verifying switches status for pools.

hh3cDHCPSvrVerifyMacEntry.name: hh3cDHCPSvrVerifyMacEntry
hh3cDHCPSvrVerifyMacEntry.description: An entry containing the switch status for a pool.

hh3cDHCPSvrVerifyMacSwitch.name: hh3cDHCPSvrVerifyMacSwitch
hh3cDHCPSvrVerifyMacSwitch.description: The switch status for this pool. It has two defined values: enabled and disabled. If the value is enabled, the DHCP server only allocates IP address to host in the MAC list. The default value is disabled.

hh3cDHCPSvrPoolMacTable.name: hh3cDHCPSvrPoolMacTable
hh3cDHCPSvrPoolMacTable.description: A table containing the MAC addresses list for pools.

hh3cDHCPSvrPoolMacEntry.name: hh3cDHCPSvrPoolMacEntry
hh3cDHCPSvrPoolMacEntry.description: An entry containing a MAC address and a mask.

hh3cDHCPSvrPoolMacOptIndex.name: hh3cDHCPSvrPoolMacOptIndex
hh3cDHCPSvrPoolMacOptIndex.description: Option group index binding for the MAC address.

hh3cDHCPSvrPoolMacRowstatus.name: hh3cDHCPSvrPoolMacRowstatus
hh3cDHCPSvrPoolMacRowstatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy.

hh3cDHCPServerAddrExhaust.name: hh3cDHCPServerAddrExhaust
hh3cDHCPServerAddrExhaust.description: This trap is generated when the device DHCP server address exhaust.

hh3cDHCPServerAddrExhaustRecover.name: hh3cDHCPServerAddrExhaustRecover
hh3cDHCPServerAddrExhaustRecover.description: This trap is generated when the device DHCP server address exhaust recover.

hh3cDHCPServerAvgIpUsageOverflow.name: hh3cDHCPServerAvgIpUsageOverflow
hh3cDHCPServerAvgIpUsageOverflow.description: This trap is generated when the average IP address usage of DHCP server pool in 5 minutes overflows.

hh3cDHCPServerMaxIpUsageOverflow.name: hh3cDHCPServerMaxIpUsageOverflow
hh3cDHCPServerMaxIpUsageOverflow.description: This trap is generated when the maximum IP address usage of DHCP server pool in 5 minutes overflows.

hh3cDHCPServerAllocateOverflow.name: hh3cDHCPServerAllocateOverflow
hh3cDHCPServerAllocateOverflow.description: This trap is generated when the number of DHCP server allocated IP address in 5 minutes overflows.
